ckModal_main_2533902\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xsz1665702892138.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xsz1665702892138.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xsz1665702892138.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xsz1665702892138\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Global Uniface COM Settings\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__global_uniface_com_settings_113628\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify global options for the COM connector.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__p_d35465e1_d35466e1_d35467e1\">Setting global COM options creates entries in the Microsoft Windows Registry.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__note_w5789ab1b5b3_w5790ab1b5_w5791ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Never modify the Windows Registry manually, because any mistakes you make can cause Windows or Uniface to malfunction, or not function at all.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__topic_d23122e1_d23123e1_d23124e1_d23125e1_d23126e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1131607e55\">\n                       \n Settings\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__li_d18197e1_d18198e1_d18199e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keep COM component in\n\t\t\t memory</span>—keep the COM component in memory when a process repeatedly calls Uniface COM\n\t\t\t objects. This speeds up COM operation and prevents memory leakage, which is particularly useful\n\t\t\t when Uniface services are being called from ASPs. \n\t\t\t <p class=\"p\">The following registry entry is created:</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__li_d18200e1_d18201e1_d18202e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Debug logging</span>—directs\n\t\t\t the COM connector to generate detailed logging to the Windows debugger channel. The logging is\n\t\t\t output using the Windows API function <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutputDebugString()</code>, so it can be seen while\n\t\t\t running under a debugger such as Visual Studio or Dependency Walker. You can also use DebugView\n\t\t\t from <a class=\"xref\" href=\"http://www.sysinternals.com/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">www.sysinternals.com</a>. The logging\n\t\t\t can be useful to check the correct working of the other COM options, as well as the general flow of\n\t\t\t COM events. \n\t\t\t <p class=\"p\">The following registry entry is created:</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__li_d18203e1_d18204e1_d18205e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Thread\n               synchronization</span>—causes the COM driver to serialize the invocation of COM\n               objects, so only one process thread can access a Uniface COM object at a time.\n               Because Uniface is currently not fully threadsafe, this option is necessary to make\n               it work in a multi-threaded COM environment without concurrency problems. <p class=\"p\">The following registry entry is\n                  created:</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xsz1665702892138__note_w5792ab1b5b5b5_w5793ab1b5b5_w5794ab1b5_w5795ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you select\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Thread synchronization</span>, you must also set the assignment\n            option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= 1</code>, otherwise it has no effect.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bog1665702719152.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</a><p>Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgr1665702879587.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the COM Connector</a><p>The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533902\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533902\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global Uniface COM Settings Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Global Uniface COM Settings Specify global options for the COM connector. Setting global COM options creates entries in the Microsoft Windows Registry. CAUTION: Never modify the Windows Registry manually, because any mistakes you make can cause Windows or Uniface to malfunction, or not function at all. Settings Keep COM component in memory —keep the COM component in memory when a process repeatedly calls Uniface COM objects. This speeds up COM operation and prevents memory leakage, which is particularly useful when Uniface services are being called from ASPs. The following registry entry is created: Debug logging —directs the COM connector to generate detailed logging to the Windows debugger channel. The logging is output using the Windows API function OutputDebugString() , so it can be seen while running under a debugger such as Visual Studio or Dependency Walker. You can also use DebugView from www.sysinternals.com . The logging can be useful to check the correct working of the other COM options, as well as the general flow of COM events. The following registry entry is created: Thread synchronization —causes the COM driver to serialize the invocation of COM objects, so only one process thread can access a Uniface COM object at a time. Because Uniface is currently not fully threadsafe, this option is necessary to make it work in a multi-threaded COM environment without concurrency problems. The following registry entry is created: Note: If you select Thread synchronization , you must also set the assignment option $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS = 1 , otherwise it has no effect. Related Links $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads. Configuring the COM Connector The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}